the big guns.


1248
01:06:06.736 --> 01:06:07.670
Oh, my God.

1249
01:06:07.704 --> 01:06:09.472
Oh.

1250
01:06:09.506 --> 01:06:12.809
Hey, this is better
than the lobster.


1251
01:06:12.842 --> 01:06:14.544
Aha.
[ laughs ]


1252
01:06:17.747 --> 01:06:21.050
Um, Ben, I--

1253
01:06:21.083 --> 01:06:23.386
Listen, I don't
mean to be rude,


1254
01:06:23.420 --> 01:06:27.023
but I'm exhausted,
and I need to sleep.


1255
01:06:28.858 --> 01:06:30.760
Want to see what I got?

1256
01:06:30.793 --> 01:06:31.828
Yeah.

1257
01:06:43.973 --> 01:06:45.742
Wow.

1258
01:06:47.544 --> 01:06:49.612
It's me,

1259
01:06:49.646 --> 01:06:52.515
but far too flattering.

1260
01:06:55.785 --> 01:06:58.921
Well, that's
how I see you.


1261
01:06:58.955 --> 01:07:00.957
Thank you.

1262
01:07:00.990 --> 01:07:03.893
Uh, all right.

1263
01:07:03.926 --> 01:07:06.496
[ groans, blows lips ]

1264
01:07:08.665 --> 01:07:10.333
[ sighs ]

1265
01:07:15.538 --> 01:07:17.807
Where did you
learn to do that?


1266
01:07:17.840 --> 01:07:19.376
I had a lot of practice.

1267
01:07:19.409 --> 01:07:21.711
My husband
was a fisherman.


1268
01:07:21.744 --> 01:07:23.446
I mean, this is amazing.

1269
01:07:23.480 --> 01:07:25.648
I'm--I'm actually
pain-free.


1270
01:07:25.682 --> 01:07:27.850
I haven't felt
this way for months.


1271
01:07:27.884 --> 01:07:28.951
[ sighs ]

1272
01:07:28.985 --> 01:07:30.987
I don't know
how to thank you.


1273
01:07:31.020 --> 01:07:35.492
Help us keep this place
the way it is.


1274
01:07:38.395 --> 01:07:39.329
Come sit.

1275
01:08:11.461 --> 01:08:12.562
I should go.

1276
01:08:12.595 --> 01:08:13.563
Why?

1277
01:08:13.596 --> 01:08:15.732
It's a small island.

1278
01:08:15.765 --> 01:08:17.634
People'll talk.

1279
01:08:17.667 --> 01:08:19.769
You're worried about
your precious reputation?


1280
01:08:19.802 --> 01:08:21.571
No.

1281
01:08:21.604 --> 01:08:23.139
I'm worried
about yours.


1282
01:08:23.172 --> 01:08:25.107
[ laughs ]

1283
01:08:25.141 --> 01:08:27.910
This is the least
judgmental place you'll
ever find, Congressman,


1284
01:08:27.944 --> 01:08:30.413
and it's been that way
for a long time.


1285
01:08:30.447 --> 01:08:35.918
Intolerance is
the least of our problems.


1286
01:08:35.952 --> 01:08:37.019
Listen...

1287
01:08:39.021 --> 01:08:42.459
I've been with
a lot of men over the years.


1288
01:08:42.492 --> 01:08:43.626
[ chuckles ]

1289
01:08:43.660 --> 01:08:46.829
I think I was chasing
that excitement,


1290
01:08:46.863 --> 01:08:50.533
that sense
of anticipation.


1291
01:08:50.567 --> 01:08:52.034
You know what I mean?

1292
01:08:54.136 --> 01:08:57.173
I think I've been lonely
for a long time, Charlie.


1293
01:08:58.941 --> 01:09:00.743
You said up
on the cliffs that you
weren't lonely.


1294
01:09:04.914 --> 01:09:07.484
I guess I lied.

1295
01:09:16.058 --> 01:09:18.795
[ bird warbles ]

1296
01:09:20.997 --> 01:09:23.566
[ bird warbles ]

1297
01:10:03.239 --> 01:10:04.240
[ explosion ]
[ gasps ]


1298
01:10:04.274 --> 01:10:06.208
[ boom echoes ]

1299
01:10:07.744 --> 01:10:09.111
What was that?

1300
01:10:25.728 --> 01:10:27.897
No!

1301
01:10:27.930 --> 01:10:30.066
No! My Sea Hag!

1302
01:10:30.099 --> 01:10:31.033
Not her!

1303
01:10:34.203 --> 01:10:35.672
No!

1304
01:10:37.907 --> 01:10:39.008
[ gasps ]

1305
01:10:39.041 --> 01:10:40.009
Matty.

1306
01:10:40.042 --> 01:10:42.712
MATTY:
No! No...


1307
01:10:42.745 --> 01:10:43.846
Whose boat is that?

1308
01:10:43.880 --> 01:10:45.247
It's the Sea Hag.

1309
01:10:45.282 --> 01:10:46.248
[ Matty yelling ]

1310
01:10:46.283 --> 01:10:47.884
Jesus Christ.
No!


1311
01:10:49.719 --> 01:10:50.687
No.

1312
01:10:52.154 --> 01:10:54.657
I-Is there anything
that we can do?


1313
01:10:54.691 --> 01:10:56.326
Yeah,
like call the police


1314
01:10:56.359 --> 01:10:58.661
or maybe the Coast Guard
or the fire department?


1315
01:10:58.695 --> 01:10:59.862
Yeah, sure.

1316
01:11:02.865 --> 01:11:04.601
WOMAN:
Was the Sea Hag.


1317
01:11:04.634 --> 01:11:08.838
[ overlapping chatter ]

1318
01:11:08.871 --> 01:11:10.740
MATTY:
Gonna be like this?


1319
01:11:10.773 --> 01:11:12.809
[ explosion ]

1320
01:11:12.842 --> 01:11:14.777
[ sobbing ]

1321
01:11:22.184 --> 01:11:23.753
JARED:
Congressman!


1322
01:11:28.791 --> 01:11:31.294
I really fucked up,
Charlie.


1323
01:11:31.328 --> 01:11:34.230
I think, uh--
I think Devereaux
was behind this.


1324
01:11:34.263 --> 01:11:35.798
Who?

1325
01:11:35.832 --> 01:11:38.134
Former
Congressman Devereaux.


1326
01:11:38.167 --> 01:11:40.903
He doesn't just represent
the other lobstermen of Maine.


1327
01:11:40.937 --> 01:11:45.975
Okay, he also works
for a multinational
seafood conglomerate.


1328
01:11:46.008 --> 01:11:48.345
Their catch,
it's less and less each year,


1329
01:11:48.378 --> 01:11:49.946
and they want
these grounds.


1330
01:11:49.979 --> 01:11:51.981
They need these grounds,
Charlie.


1331
01:11:52.014 --> 01:11:53.683
Where did I fit in?

1332
01:11:59.021 --> 01:12:02.325
They wanted me
to make sure


1333
01:12:02.359 --> 01:12:05.695
that you didn't end up
defending these people.


1334
01:12:05.728 --> 01:12:08.765
So you hitched
your wagon to him
for what?


1335
01:12:08.798 --> 01:12:10.733
Why?

1336
01:12:10.767 --> 01:12:11.968
What was the price?

1337
01:12:12.001 --> 01:12:13.102
Your seat.

1338
01:12:17.206 --> 01:12:18.375
And I'm sorry.

1339
01:12:22.178 --> 01:12:23.112
Wow.

1340
01:12:24.881 --> 01:12:26.215
Wow.

1341
01:12:28.985 --> 01:12:32.088
You know he's probably
bought Deidre Macavoy,
too, don't you?


1342
01:12:37.059 --> 01:12:38.795
Listen, Charlie,
that's not it.


1343
01:12:38.828 --> 01:12:40.897
He's--He's got plans,
okay?


1344
01:12:40.930 --> 01:12:42.899
For you, for this island.

1345
01:12:42.932 --> 01:12:47.670
He's got a boatload
of media coming up here
to expose these people.


1346
01:12:47.704 --> 01:12:49.406
When will they get here?

1347
01:12:49.439 --> 01:12:50.973
Sometime soon.

1348
01:12:54.243 --> 01:12:56.713
Is that all, Jared?

1349
01:12:58.047 --> 01:12:59.782
Yeah.

1350
01:13:05.154 --> 01:13:07.990
I want a helicopter
here at 9 A.M.


1351
01:13:26.776 --> 01:13:28.711
[ footsteps ]

1352
01:13:33.883 --> 01:13:34.851
[ door opens ]

1353
01:13:34.884 --> 01:13:37.487
Hey.

1354
01:13:37.520 --> 01:13:41.023
Listen, I'm--I'm gonna
have to borrow these
for a couple days.


1355
01:13:41.057 --> 01:13:42.859
Nah, you can keep 'em.

1356
01:13:57.407 --> 01:13:59.376
Look, why don't--
Why don't you


1357
01:13:59.409 --> 01:14:02.244
come down to Washington
sometime, you know,


1358
01:14:02.279 --> 01:14:05.147
come for a visit?

1359
01:14:05.181 --> 01:14:07.249
Really?
Yeah.


1360
01:14:07.284 --> 01:14:10.453
Come, uh,
see the National
Portrait Gallery.


1361
01:14:10.487 --> 01:14:13.890
You know, your stuff
will probably be
hanging there someday.


1362
01:14:19.195 --> 01:14:21.298
All right.

1363
01:14:21.331 --> 01:14:24.100
Yeah, maybe, uh--

1364
01:14:24.133 --> 01:14:26.769
maybe when
lobster season ends.


1365
01:14:29.005 --> 01:14:32.008
Did you want this,
or...


1366
01:14:32.041 --> 01:14:34.176
Yeah. Are you kidding?

1367
01:14:35.578 --> 01:14:38.448
Thank you.

1368
01:14:38.481 --> 01:14:39.882
Mm-hmm.

1369
01:14:41.451 --> 01:14:44.086
So everything's cool,
okay?


1370
01:14:45.488 --> 01:14:47.123
All right.

1371
01:14:47.156 --> 01:14:49.091
I'll see you.

1372
01:14:49.125 --> 01:14:50.760
Good luck.

1373
01:14:55.332 --> 01:14:57.266
[ music playing ]

1374
01:15:01.137 --> 01:15:03.072
[ indistinct chatter ]

1375
01:15:16.586 --> 01:15:20.022
Jared Barnes?
What happened to you?


1376
01:15:20.056 --> 01:15:22.292
Look, Laird's been
trying to reach you
all day.


1377
01:15:22.325 --> 01:15:24.894
You gotta talk to him,
and you gotta
talk to him now.


1378
01:15:24.927 --> 01:15:27.464
Shh. Okay.
Just calm down, okay?


1379
01:15:27.497 --> 01:15:29.899
Hey, listen, is there
a Starbucks around?


1380
01:15:29.932 --> 01:15:30.900
No.

1381
01:15:30.933 --> 01:15:31.901
I gotta get
a cappuccino.


1382
01:15:31.934 --> 01:15:32.869
There isn't.

1383
01:15:35.037 --> 01:15:38.074
LAIRD: Are you still
with me all the way?


1384
01:15:38.107 --> 01:15:40.076
You're home free
for the nomination.


1385
01:15:40.109 --> 01:15:42.845
Charlie's toast.

1386
01:15:42.879 --> 01:15:45.081
Oh, right,
you're for me, Laird?


1387
01:15:45.114 --> 01:15:49.118
What about your
other pet candidate,
Deidre Macavoy?


1388
01:15:49.151 --> 01:15:50.587
Diedre's
the diversion.


1389
01:15:50.620 --> 01:15:52.355
For God's sake,
Charlie's gonna
be expelled,


1390
01:15:52.389 --> 01:15:54.857
and when he does,
you're gonna get
the nomination,


1391
01:15:54.891 --> 01:15:56.826
and you're gonna
have to step up.


1392
01:15:58.595 --> 01:16:00.630
So they're, um--

1393
01:16:00.663 --> 01:16:03.265
they're really
doing it, huh?
They're gonna expel him?


1394
01:16:03.300 --> 01:16:05.468
Expel him?
Hell, they're gonna
crucify him.


1395
01:16:05.502 --> 01:16:09.272
For God's sake, he's
been doing that Nazi
salute for 24 hours.


1396
01:16:09.306 --> 01:16:10.407
All America's seen it.

1397
01:16:10.440 --> 01:16:12.409
It's not
a Nazi salute, okay?


1398
01:16:12.442 --> 01:16:14.577
American kids were
doing that for years


1399
01:16:14.611 --> 01:16:17.046
while they recited
the Pledge of Allegiance.


1400
01:16:17.079 --> 01:16:18.581
It's called
the Bellamy salute.


1401
01:16:18.615 --> 01:16:20.550
Well, you tell that
to the American people.


1402
01:16:20.583 --> 01:16:23.052
Look, I gotta go,
but when you get back


1403
01:16:23.085 --> 01:16:25.054
to civilization,
give me a call.


1404
01:16:25.087 --> 01:16:27.624
I got something special
for you.


1405
01:16:27.657 --> 01:16:29.992
Yeah.

1406
01:16:49.145 --> 01:16:52.214
No, no, no, no, no,
no, no, no, no, no!


1407
01:16:52.248 --> 01:16:54.016
That was mine!
[ splash ]


1408
01:16:55.718 --> 01:16:57.454
That was mine!

1409
01:16:57.487 --> 01:16:58.555
Go get it.

1410
01:17:08.998 --> 01:17:11.200
Well...

1411
01:17:11.233 --> 01:17:12.402
see ya.

1412
01:17:12.435 --> 01:17:14.003
Yep.

1413
01:17:19.075 --> 01:17:21.311
Why don't you come
down to Washington,


1414
01:17:21.344 --> 01:17:24.514
see where this can go?

1415
01:17:24.547 --> 01:17:27.249
Are you joking?

1416
01:17:27.284 --> 01:17:29.286
No, I'm not.

1417
01:17:29.319 --> 01:17:31.621
I'd rather have
a lobotomy. Heh heh.


1418
01:17:31.654 --> 01:17:33.022
Why?

1419
01:17:33.055 --> 01:17:36.058
Well, I will tell you
why, Mr. Winship.


1420
01:17:36.092 --> 01:17:38.160
In some ways,
you remind me
of Jimmy Stewart


1421
01:17:38.194 --> 01:17:40.963
in "It's
a Wonderful Life."


1422
01:17:40.997 --> 01:17:44.033
Do you remember how
he spent his entire life


1423
01:17:44.066 --> 01:17:46.369
trying to protect
his beautiful
Bedford Falls


1424
01:17:46.403 --> 01:17:48.971
from the evil
Mr. Potter?


1425
01:17:49.005 --> 01:17:52.241
Yeah. Zuzu's petals.

1426
01:17:52.275 --> 01:17:57.046
That's Pottersville,
at least to me.


1427
01:17:57.079 --> 01:17:58.481
[ helicopter whirring ]

1428
01:17:58.515 --> 01:18:00.683
Can you understand?

1429
01:18:02.118 --> 01:18:04.354
Yes, I think I can.

1430
01:18:06.489 --> 01:18:10.293
Sounds like the bus
to Pottersville is here.


1431
01:18:11.761 --> 01:18:13.330
Yep.

1432
01:18:15.298 --> 01:18:17.367
Why don't you stay here,
Congressman?


1433
01:18:17.400 --> 01:18:20.136
[ laughs ]
And do what?


1434
01:18:20.169 --> 01:18:23.340
Ah, I've been thinking
about cutting back
on my portfolio.


1435
01:18:23.373 --> 01:18:26.509
I might
be persuaded to give up
the garbage concession.


1436
01:18:26.543 --> 01:18:28.745
Now that's something
to look forward to.


1437
01:18:48.431 --> 01:18:51.568
You're up against
some serious predators.


1438
01:18:51.601 --> 01:18:55.272
Well, we've weathered
bigger storms than this
in the past 400 years.


1439
01:18:55.305 --> 01:18:56.573
I know you have.

1440
01:18:56.606 --> 01:18:58.608
I'll do what I can
for you in Washington.


1441
01:18:58.641 --> 01:19:00.042
You've all
taught me a lot.


1442
01:19:01.143 --> 01:19:02.144
Thanks.

1443
01:19:02.178 --> 01:19:03.280
Thank you.

1444
01:19:05.081 --> 01:19:06.383
Hey!

1445
01:19:06.416 --> 01:19:09.619
Come on back, son.
We got it all here.


1446
01:19:11.521 --> 01:19:14.090
Every day
is different.


1447
01:19:16.793 --> 01:19:18.728
[ engine warming up ]

1448
01:19:20.797 --> 01:19:24.166
Charlie! Charlie!

1449
01:19:24.200 --> 01:19:25.735
Hey!

1450
01:19:25.768 --> 01:19:28.538
I still need
to book the tickets
for Washington.


1451
01:19:28.571 --> 01:19:30.340
I'm not going to Washington.

1452
01:19:30.373 --> 01:19:31.508
What?

1453
01:19:31.541 --> 01:19:33.175
I'm going back
to my district.


1454
01:19:33.209 --> 01:19:35.244
Call Abigail. Tell her
I'm having a town meeting


1455
01:19:35.278 --> 01:19:36.846
at the local high school
in Bedford.


1456
01:19:36.879 --> 01:19:38.515
No, no, no.

1457
01:19:38.548 --> 01:19:41.083
Bedford
is Deidre Macavoy's
home base, Charlie.


1458
01:19:41.117 --> 01:19:43.286
They'll tear you
apart there.


1459
01:19:43.320 --> 01:19:44.287
Probably.

1460
01:19:44.321 --> 01:19:45.622
Just do it.

1461
01:19:48.791 --> 01:19:50.727
[ music playing ]

1462
01:20:34.404 --> 01:20:36.473
[ all shouting ]
Congressman Winship,


1463
01:20:36.506 --> 01:20:38.174
are you going
to resign today?


1464
01:20:38.207 --> 01:20:39.376
No.

1465
01:20:39.409 --> 01:20:40.377
[ overlapping chatter ]

1466
01:20:40.410 --> 01:20:43.179
Congressman,
are you a Nazi?


1467
01:20:43.212 --> 01:20:45.582
Congressman Randolph
has accused you of
disloyalty to the flag.


1468
01:20:45.615 --> 01:20:47.417
He has a right
to his opinion.


1469
01:20:48.518 --> 01:20:50.219
Hey, guys,
right this way.


1470
01:20:50.252 --> 01:20:51.588
Okay.

1471
01:20:51.621 --> 01:20:53.856
[ sighs ] We are riding
the whirlwind now.


1472
01:20:53.890 --> 01:20:55.257
Not exactly riding it.

1473
01:20:55.292 --> 01:20:57.193
This is the best
I could do.


1474
01:20:57.226 --> 01:21:00.697
This high school was
kind enough to donate
their space, so...


1475
01:21:00.730 --> 01:21:02.799
You flew
all the way up here
just for this?


1476
01:21:02.832 --> 01:21:04.634
Oh, I wouldn't
have missed it.


1477
01:21:04.667 --> 01:21:06.703
This is the first
public execution
I've actually ever seen.


1478
01:21:06.736 --> 01:21:08.838
Oh, thank you.
[ laughs ]


1479
01:21:08.871 --> 01:21:10.807
I'm gonna walk
a little bit.


1480
01:21:12.809 --> 01:21:17.914
Well, it turns out that
Congressman Winship is
right about one thing.


1481
01:21:17.947 --> 01:21:20.483
Until Nazi Germany
declared war on the U.S.,


1482
01:21:20.517 --> 01:21:24.487
American schoolchildren
recited the Pledge of Allegiance


1483
01:21:24.521 --> 01:21:28.658
every morning while delivering
the Nazi stiff-armed salute.


1484
01:21:33.530 --> 01:21:36.433
[ cellphone ringing ]

1485
01:21:36.466 --> 01:21:37.800
Hey, Harlan.

1486
01:21:37.834 --> 01:21:39.869
Ah, I got some bad news
for you, son.


1487
01:21:39.902 --> 01:21:42.305
I thought
you'd want to know.


1488
01:21:42.339 --> 01:21:44.307
Mississippi
has seceded again?


1489
01:21:44.341 --> 01:21:46.943
[ laughs ]
That'd be good news.


1490
01:21:46.976 --> 01:21:49.211
I've-
-Oh, wait a second.

1491
01:21:51.314 --> 01:21:55.652
The committee
voted to authorize
an expulsion motion.


1492
01:21:55.685 --> 01:22:01.658
Now, right now, I'd say
the full House vote is
a foregone conclusion.


1493
01:22:01.691 --> 01:22:04.527
So what
are my high crimes
and misdemeanors?


1494
01:22:04.561 --> 01:22:07.364
Flagrant disobedience
of House rules,


1495
01:22:07.397 --> 01:22:10.633
conduct unbecoming
a sitting member,


1496
01:22:10.667 --> 01:22:14.671
equating the Pledge
of Allegiance
with "Mein Kampf."


1497
01:22:14.704 --> 01:22:17.006
How did you vote?

1498
01:22:17.039 --> 01:22:20.543
[ scoffs ]
Now, how do you think?


1499
01:22:20.577 --> 01:22:22.445
Thanks, Harlan.

1500
01:22:22.479 --> 01:22:23.880
Now, a lot of people
around here


1501
01:22:23.913 --> 01:22:25.882
don't like
what's going on here,


1502
01:22:25.915 --> 01:22:28.485
but they're
running scared.


1503
01:22:28.518 --> 01:22:30.787
It-
-It's like a sickness.

1504
01:22:30.820 --> 01:22:32.555
Personally,
I think we're headed


1505
01:22:32.589 --> 01:22:36.293
into a kind of moral
and political ice age.


1506
